.TH "MEDIAERROR.MESSAGE" "3JS" "July 24, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
MediaError.message \- MediaError: message property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only property \f[B]\f[CB]MediaError.message\f[B]\f[R] returns
a human\-readable string offering specific diagnostic details related to
the error described by the \f[CR]MediaError\f[R] object, or an empty
string (\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R]) if no diagnostic information can be
determined or provided.
.SH VALUE
A string providing a detailed, specific explanation of what went wrong
and possibly how it might be fixed.
This is \f[I]not\f[R] a generic description of the
\f[CR]MediaError.code\f[R] property\(cqs value, but instead goes deeper
into the specifics of this particular error and its circumstances.
If no specific details are available, this string is empty.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Logging MediaError messages
This example creates an \f[CR]<audio>\f[R] element, establishes an error
handler for it, then lets the user click buttons to choose whether to
assign a valid audio file or a missing file to the element\(cqs
\f[CR]src\f[R] attribute.
The error handler outputs log lines to a box onscreen describing the
error, including the \f[CR]code\f[R], the \f[CR]message\f[R], and a hint
that may be more useful for visitors than the diagnostic
\f[CR]message\f[R]:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]audio\f[R] controls id=\(dqaudio\(dq></\f[B]audio\f[R]>
<\f[B]div\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqvalid\-button\(dq>Valid file</\f[B]button\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqinvalid\-button\(dq>Missing file</\f[B]button\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqsvg\-button\(dq>Wrong format</\f[B]button\f[R]>
</\f[B]div\f[R]>
<\f[B]pre\f[R] id=\(dqlog\(dq>Logs:</\f[B]pre\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
The example creates an \f[CR]<audio>\f[R] element and lets the user
assign either a valid music file to it, or a link to a file which
doesn\(cqt exist.
This lets us see the behavior of the \f[CR]error\f[R] event handler,
which is received by an event handler we add to the \f[CR]<audio>\f[R]
element itself.
.PP
First, it gets the \f[CR]MediaError\f[R] object describing the error
from the \f[CR]error\f[R] property on the \f[CR]HTMLAudioElement\f[R]
representing the audio player.
The error\(cqs numeric \f[CR]code\f[R] is checked against
\f[CR]MediaError\f[R] constants, which are initially undefined.
If the \f[CR]err.code\f[R] is equal to any constant, it creates a
generic hint with \f[CR]MediaError.message\f[R] added to the log line to
provide more detailed diagnostic information for developers.
The resulting text is added to the \f[CR]<pre>\f[R] element:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] audioElement = document.getElementById(\(dqaudio\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] validButton = document.getElementById(\(dqvalid\-button\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] invalidButton = document.getElementById(\(dqinvalid\-button\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] svgButton = document.getElementById(\(dqsvg\-button\(dq);

\f[B]const\f[R] logMessage = (logLine) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] now = \f[B]new\f[R] Date();
  \f[B]const\f[R] timestamp = now.toLocaleTimeString();
  document.getElementById(\(dqlog\(dq).innerText += \(ga\(rsn[${timestamp}] ${logLine}\(ga;
};

validButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  audioElement.src = \(dqhttps://mdn.github.io/shared\-assets/audio/guitar.mp3\(dq;
});

svgButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  audioElement.src =
    \(dqhttps://mdn.github.io/shared\-assets/images/examples/dino.svg\(dq;
});

invalidButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  audioElement.src = \(dqno\-file\-here.mp3\(dq;
});

audioElement.onerror = () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] err = audioElement.error;
  \f[B]let\f[R] userHint = \(dq\(dq;

  \f[B]switch\f[R] (err.code) {
    \f[B]case\f[R] MediaError.MEDIA_ERR_ABORTED:
      userHint = \(dqCanceled audio playback.\(dq;
      \f[B]break\f[R];
    \f[B]case\f[R] MediaError.MEDIA_ERR_NETWORK:
      userHint = \(dqA network error occurred while fetching the audio.\(dq;
      \f[B]break\f[R];
    \f[B]case\f[R] MediaError.MEDIA_ERR_DECODE:
      userHint = \(dqAn error occurred while decoding the audio.\(dq;
      \f[B]break\f[R];
    \f[B]case\f[R] MediaError.MEDIA_ERR_SRC_NOT_SUPPORTED:
      userHint = \(dqAudio is missing or is an unsupported format.\(dq;
      \f[B]break\f[R];
    \f[B]default\f[R]:
      userHint += \(dqAn unknown error occurred.\(dq;
      \f[B]break\f[R];
  }

  \f[B]const\f[R] message = err.message || \(dqno message available\(dq;

  logMessage(\(gaError code ${err.code} (${err.message}), ${userHint}\(ga);
};
.EE
.PP
Click the \(lqValid file\(rq button to start playback as expected, the
\(lqMissing file\(rq button to try to load a missing resource, and the
\(lqWrong format\(rq button to try to set an SVG file as the source for
the audio element.
Comparing the log output for the two error cases illustrates the
difference between a \f[CR]MediaError\f[R]\(cqs \f[CR]code\f[R] and
\f[CR]message\f[R]:
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]MediaError\f[R]: Interface used to define the
\f[CR]MediaError.message\f[R] property
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]<audio>\f[R], \f[CR]<video>\f[R]
